Thanks Fogo folks - once I digest my 2 - 3 lbs of meat, I'll be back to see you again!

Wow, this dinner was pretty spectacular.
I've never had an experience quite like it.
So, you start with a lovely salad bar, they had butter lettuce (yessss) and a delicious basil dressing that went great with my tomato slices.
There were also a variety of cheeses available and smoked salmon, yum!
Now lets get down to the meat.
There was a Picanha (the prime part of the sirloin) which was gorgeous, Filet Mignon, Beef Ancho, Lombo (pork loin filets encrusted with parmesan cheese!
), Frango chicken wrapped in bacon...yay, Linguica (slow-roasted pork sausages) and my favorite, Cordeiro, the leg of lamb, moist and delicious!
This is a great concept for a restaurant, I can't wait to bring my husband for his birthday!

I am late in reviewing this but still felt a need to voice off on what a fantastic evening I had.
The food was amazing.
There was a excellent salad bar with items such as mozzarella, roasted red peppers, salmon, asparagus, marinated mushrooms and all sorts of salads.
One could honestly fill up on one circle of the salad bar, but I was careful to save room for the delicious meats.
The selection of meat was incredible, from what I can remember: bacon wrapped filet mignon, top sirloin, lamb chops and leg of lamb, chicken in garlic, sausage, pork ribs, bacon wrapped chicken and on and on.
The sides were great too, crispy polenta, mashed potatoes and caramelized bananas.
What really made this night special was the amazing service.
We were given a tour of the kitchen so we got to see how it was all prepared.
Our server was also quick to make sure we were able to taste every meat selection they had, and to send the guys over had we requested more of a particular item.
This was a 5 star dining experience and I will definitely be back.
Thanks Gabi!

The whole Fogo de Chao experience is really unique, fun, and delicious.
They have a fresh and tasty buffet style salad bar with items such as, pasta salads, asparagus, fresh bread, fruit, and all sorts of side items.
The variety of meat is phenomenal with chicken, filet mignons, rib eyes, etc.
Wow!
Is this place good.
I highly recommend for small groups,  big parties, whoever!

